        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Looks like this breaks lazydev.nvim as it uses `Lua = ...`. See https://github.com/folke/lazydev.nvim/blob/ff2cbcba459b637ec3fd165a2be59b7bbaeedf0d/lua/lazydev/workspace.lua#L189-L200\r\n\r\nThis is a slightly breaking for users used to have `Lua = ...` in their setting.\r\n\r\nIs it new design of emmylua? I am using `0.22.0`, maybe we should use `Lua = ...` if it's still compatible with emmylua.\r\n\r\nEDIT: ah I saw there's already a pr for this: https://github.com/folke/lazydev.nvim/pull/141",
